Rating: 3
I love this recipe. It was so easy. I cut the sugar by a half cup because i didn't want them to be super sweet. They came out more cake- like than fudgey but the were still very yummy. Love the subtle espresso and cinnamon flavors. Also, i didn't have white chocolate so i just used semi sweet chips for the ganache and it turned out perfect.

Rating: 4
I made these as part of my holiday baking treats for work and friends. A major hit, especially with my boss. I love the coffee essence and the rich ganache. Best when served in little bite sizes...I find the tray empties fast that way. I will make these again, definitely.

